"title": "1225: God, as Spirit",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1225: god, as spirit",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God has no material body and he is not subject to human limitations. While his spiritual nature is clearly inferred in Scripture, it is seldom directly stated; the emphasis is on his dynamic, living personhood.</p>\n<h2>God as spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:24\">JHN 4:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:5-Isa28:6\">ISA 28:5–28:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:3\">ISA 31:3</a></p>\n<h3>God is not subject to physical limitations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:27\">1KI 18:27</a> <em>Elijah's mockery of Baal implies a contrast with the true God who is not subject to the limitations suggested</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:4-Job10:8\">JOB 10:4–10:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:3-Ps121:4\">PSA 121:3–121:4</a></p>\n<h3>God as the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:7\">PSA 139:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:11\">PSA 51:11</a> <em>The Spirit and the presence of God are equated</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:10\">PSA 143:10</a> <em>God's guidance and the Spirit's leading are equated</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:16\">ISA 34:16</a> <em>God's Spirit participates in God's plans</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:17–3:18</a></p>\n<h2>God cannot be represented physically</h2>\n<h3>Images of God are prohibited</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:4\">EXO 20:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:17\">EXO 34:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:1\">LEV 26:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:29\">ACT 17:29</a></p>\n<h3>God transcends spacial limitations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:27\">1KI 8:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:18\">2CH 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:6\">2CH 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:48-Acts7:50\">ACT 7:48–7:50</a></p>\n<h3>God is invisible</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15-1Tim6:16\">1TI 6:15–6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:20\">EXO 33:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:15-Deut4:19\">DEU 4:15–4:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a></p>",
